videos.description: Running the option, Clinton Lynch gets the pitch and a lane to run through going 42 yards to the house putting Georgia Tech up on Georgia 7-0.
videos.headline: Lynch goes 42 yards to strike first for Georgia Tech

videos.description: Georgia Tech tries to run the throw back to QB Justin Thomas, but Qua Searcy keeps it himself and dives for the end zone to give the Yellow Jackets the touchdown that gives them the win after the ensuing extra point.
videos.headline: Broken gadget play still scores winning TD for Georgia Tech
